<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>2 SPEED AND DOUBLE REDUCTION SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - ADJUST/INSTALL - INSTALL DIFFERENTIAL AND RING GEAR
        ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTALL DIFFERENTIAL AND RING GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Lubricate bearings during the following assembly procedures. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in
                    the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubes.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place ring gear and differential assembly in carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401640">Figure 40</hotlnk>). Insure that ring gear and drive pinion mesh properly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401640" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401640" filename="../figg14/G1401640.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Differential Installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>During installation, tilt carrier to allow support case pilot to rest in carrier bore, then
                        install bearing cup as shown in illustration. Also install bearing cup on opposite side of
                        differential.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When installing bearing caps and adjusters, exercise care not to cross threads.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install bearing adjusters and caps.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install and tighten bearing cap bolts finger tight. If this is difficult, use a hand
                wrench.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
